                <p class="mb-4">
                    When you refer to Level 3 design, this might indicate a specific stage in the automotive design process, which generally includes several stages of development and refinement.

                    In automotive engineering, Level 3 design might refer to a higher level of detail in the design, focusing on more precise engineering and prototyping. Here's a breakdown of how the design process typically works:
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Level 1: Concept Design:
                    Initial sketches and broad concepts.
                    Focus on aesthetics, feasibility, and basic functionality.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Level 2: Detailed Design:
                    Refinement of components.
                    Initial CAD (Computer-Aided Design) models created.
                    Preliminary simulations for aerodynamics, structural integrity, and ergonomics.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Level 3: Prototype and Final Design:
